Our rapidly growing team is headquartered in the heart of Atlanta’s vibrant tech community and is led by former operators from Amazon, XPO, Ryder, Coyote, Convoy, and Manhattan Associates. Stord is backed by over $325M in funding from Kleiner Perkins, BOND, Founders Fund, D1 Capital, Salesforce Ventures, Susa Ventures, Lux Capital, Lineage Logistics, and Franklin Templeton Investments at a unicorn valuation of over $1.3 billion.

Come help us help businesses out-deliver their competition with Cloud Supply Chain.

About the Senior Software Engineer Position:

We are looking for a seasoned engineer who enjoys the scale and complexity that comes with building large scale distributed systems, and has the battle scars to prove it! Someone who can think about long term strategic impact and balance that with effective tactical execution. Someone who develops systems with operational excellence in mind, continually refactors to ensure long term system viability and efficiency. Someone who builds to catch problems before they occur with observability and maintainability in mind. Someone who is genuinely interested in disrupting the supply chain industry and making a big dent in the universe. If this sounds like you, please read on. We have some additional guidelines for what makes a good candidate for this role.

What you’ll Do:

You will be working with the group that builds, maintains, and owns the Order Management Service (OMS) Product which is part of the Stord One Commerce suite of products and tools. These products help power an innovative and world class logistics network.

What You'll Need:

7+ years of experience in software development
Great track record of delivering high quality software solutions during hyper growth
Solid understanding of lean and agile software development practices
Strong grasp of cloud native and distributed software development principles
Experience with Kubernetes and modern software deployment principles
Good understanding of “soup to nuts” of end to end software development life cycle
Ability to up-level and grow other engineers within the organization
Humility to accept mistakes and learn from them
Strong in operational excellence and a data informed decision maker
Be a strong partner to Engineering-Product-Design leadership
Bonus Points:

Supply Chain Background
Ruby/Rails, React, and/or Elixir
Functional Programming Experience
Based in the Greater Atlanta Area
Culture Snapshot:

Our team is passionate about sitting at the intersection of enterprise technology and global logistics. The Stord company culture is electric, and we are proud to offer a career experience that will make you excited to come to work every day. We are creating an environment of continuous improvement through collaboration and diverse thinking by solving challenging problems and working with talented and smart colleagues. At Stord you will have daily opportunities to learn and inspire those around you. You will be surrounded by a team of self-starters who are motivated to have an impact through driving results.

Below are a few perks of joining our team:

Competitive salary and bonus
Friendly, Passionate, and Intelligent Employee Base
Creative Problem Solving and Entrepreneurial Thinking
Fast-Paced Environment
Low-Ego, Solution-Driven Culture
Community Involvement and Volunteer Opportunities
Employee Resource Groups: Women of Stord, JEDI (Justice, Equity, Diversity, & Inclusion), Stord-Serves, & More
Benefits:

401(k)
Medical, Dental, and Vision Insurance
Life and Disability Insurance
